EXTRACTED VALUE: The most glaring problems with the game arise in human AI and weird graphical hiccups. Human AI, sorry to say, is dumb.
An extremely uncomplicated title that has its fair share of fun due to the hilariously brutal combat animations.
An average shooter that has the ability to be great, but misses out by not using its namesake correctly.
More of a solid foundation than a groundbreaking game, Blue Dragon still offers plenty to do. Here's hoping for a bit more punch to the sequel.
If I had to sum Mercenaries up in one word, I would say “fun.” If I had to sum it up in five, I would say “fun but glitchy as hell!”
When heading online you’ll find some much needed variety that wasn’t present in the single player game.
An excellent shooter that maintains the series' sterling rep, but where are the new ideas? [Nov 2008, p.76]
